[http://www.mutt.org/ Mutt] is an email client.

The [http://www.drao-ofr.hia-iha.nrc-cnrc.gc.ca/~rreid/software/mutt/mutt.el original download] is no longer active (2025). 

There is a more up-to-date (2019) Mutt Mode by Felix Weilbach hosted here: https://gitlab.com/flexw/mutt-mode

The 1.4 version of mutt.el by Eric Kidd (1998) can be found here on the wiki: Lisp:mutt.el. (ed note: this appears to be what was linked to in the original download; see [https://web.archive.org/web/20040816073016/http://www.drao-ofr.hia-iha.nrc-cnrc.gc.ca/~rreid/software/mutt/mutt.el Wayback Machine link ]).

An earlier version of Eric Kidd's mutt.el (1.1) can be found here: http://www.lemis.com/grog/programs/emacs/emacs/mutt.el

== Installation:==

Put mutt.el in your load-path and add the following line to the .emacs file:

 (require 'mutt)

See Also MuttInEmacs.



